    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This collection consists of ca. 300 black and white, 35mm slides; the images are of Spanish Civil War-era Spain and include scenes of wartime destruction, refugees, street and battlefield scenes, a bullfight, and village life.  There are also a few shots of naval vessels on the coast of North Africa and a few images of snowy mountains.  The many shots of Nationalist troops, Spanish officials, and individuals in German uniform suggest that the photographs might have been taken by a German visitor, touring Spain toward the end of, or just after, the Civil War. The slides were the property of Eric Muller, a  professional photographer from Lynn, MA, who got them from a returning U.S. serviceman who had served in Europe in World War II.</field>
    <field name="acqinfo_teim">300 slides were donated by Norman Muller in 2002. An additional 8 slides were donated by Norman Muller in 2012. The accession number associated with this gift is 2013.048</field>
    <field name="custodhist_teim">The slides were donated to the Tamiment Library by Eric Muller's son, Norman E. Muller in 2002.</field>
